Detailed Description

template<class _Container>
class WVariable< _Container >

This class works as a controller for the SESWrapper variables.

The main member functions are set() and get() which act as class callbacks through the Command design pattern [Gamma et. al.].

See also:
WSESWrapperBase

Calls the getter for the variable.

Parameters:
[in]indexAn index used for variables of vector or array types.
[out]valueA pointer to the value to obtain. For vectors or arrays, this can usually be 0 (NULL), in which case size is modified to request the size of the vector/array.
[in,out]sizeThe size of the value, if that value is a vector or array.
Returns:
Usually WError::ERR_OK on success, otherwise an error code.
